The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, July 25: The government has approved 12 projects worth Rs 2,643 crore under the public-private partnership scheme in infrastructure. Approximately Rs 529.78 crore will be provided as viability gap funding (VGF) by the government, an official release said. The exact VGF support will, however, be decided on the basis of a competitive bidding. 

 New Delhi, July 25: The finance ministry has clarified that interest income on bank deposits, national savings certificates, bonds and debentures of PSU companies is liable to tax even if the amount is below Rs 12,000. This has happened because section 80L of the Income Tax Act, providing for deduction of Rs 12,000 on income by ways of interest from these instruments have been abolished from the assessment year 2006-07. The ministry in a statement advised taxpayers to ensure that such income is taken into account while filing the return of income for assessment year 2006-07.

 Mumbai, July 25: Zee Telefilms has got shareholders? nod for the demerger of its news business undertaking to Zee News and cable business undertakings with Siti Cable Network to Wire and Wireless Ltd.

 Mumbai, July 25: US-based E*trade Financial Corporation has acquired a controlling stake in brokerage firm IL amp;FS Investsmart Ltd. It plans to raise its equity stake in the company and increase management participation.




